comments.body:
[~jloza] I should have tired to reproduce your problem first! I couldn't! I replaced "Deny" with "Booger" in a policy, pressed "save changes" and got an error notification of "Error in uploaded policy: { "Version": "2011-04-01", "Statement": [ { "Action": "*", "Resource": "*", "Effect": "Allow" }, { "Action": "iam:*", "Resource": "*", "Effect": "Booger" } ] }"

I then viewed my policy again and it shows:

  "Version": "2011-04-01",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Action": "*",
      "Resource": "*",
      "Effect": "Allow"
    },
    {
      "Action": "iam:*",
      "Resource": "*",
      "Effect": "Deny"
    }
  ]
}

So, it seems to be non-destructive. If you can reproduce this, please supply as many details as possible. I was using the team dev cloud which is slightly out of date with testing.

[~dkavanagh]: Pull request 751 looks good except for the error messages display.  Would prefer we change it to the following

{code}
error_messages = '. '.join(self.create_form.get_errors_list())
{code}

Verified on: eucaconsole-4.0.0-0.0.468.20140606gitc323a3aa.el6.noarch

I received this error when I changed "Allow" to "Accept":
{code}
Error in uploaded policy: { "Version": "2012-10-17", "Statement": [ { "Action": "ec2:*", "Resource": "*", "Effect": "Allow" }, { "Action": "elasticloadbalancing:*", "Resource": "*", "Effect": "Allow" }, { "Action": "autoscaling:*", "Resource": "*", "Effect": "Allow" }, { "Action": "cloudwatch:*", "Resource": "*", "Effect": "Accept" }, { "Action": "s3:*", "Resource": "*", "Effect": "Allow" }, { "Action": "iam:*", "Resource": "*", "Effect": "Allow" }, { "Action": "sts:*", "Resource": "*", "Effect": "Allow" } ] }
{code}
I also received the other errors described above when adding invalid characters.

I was able to modify the policy without starting over and save the changes.
